  "web3_minning_home_slogan": "Stake GT to Earn High and Stable Returns",
  "web3_minning_home_stake_now": "Stake Now",
  "web3_minning_home_return_trend": "7-Day Return Trend",
  "web3_minning_static_apr_desc": "Static return refers to the simple annualized return (APR) based on the staked principal, without compounding effects. \nDaily returns are dynamically generated based on block growth. The formula for calculating static return is: Yesterday's Total Network Reward × 365 ÷ Total Network Staked Amount.",
  "web3_minning_home_step1_desc": "Select a node, enter the amount, and start staking.",
  "web3_minning_home_step2_desc": "Earn stable returns, with the flexibility of switching between nodes.",
  "web3_minning_home_step3_title": "Redeem GT Anytime",
  "web3_minning_home_step3_desc": "Supports GT redemption at any time for peace of mind.",
  "web3_minning_home_faq1_title": "What is GT Staking?",
  "web3_minning_home_faq1_desc": "GT Staking is a mechanism where users earn rewards by staking GT (platform token). Users can stake GT to a node that is actively participating in consensus process to earn block rewards. The node will then allocate its earnings to users based on their staked amounts.",
  "web3_minning_home_faq2_title": "How are rewards earned?",
  "web3_minning_home_faq2_desc": "Your rewards come from the block rewards earned by your selected node. Each block distributes a total reward of 0.4 GT, which is allocated among three randomly selected nodes based on certain ratios. After receiving the reward, the node distributes it to users based on their staking proportion. You can view your current earnings anytime on the \"My Assets\" page.",
  "web3_minning_home_faq3_title": "Why hasn't my staking generate returns yet?",
  "web3_minning_home_faq3_desc": "Possible reasons include: \n1. Low block production probability: The node may have insufficient stake or a low score, resulting in not being selected for block production.\n2. Recently staked: Rewards are produced dynamically; a delay is normal.\n3. Node performance issues: Node downtime or instability may temporarily prevent block production.\n4. Network settlement delays: In rare cases, system settlement may be slightly delayed.",
  "web3_minning_home_faq4_title": "Can I redeem my staked GT at any time?",
  "web3_minning_home_faq4_desc": "Yes, GT Staking supports flexible redemption. You can request redemption on the 'My Staking' page under the staked nodes section. Once the transaction is confirmed on-chain, your full staked GT and any accrued rewards will be returned.",
  "web3_minning_home_faq5_title": "Are there risks involved in GT Staking?",
  "web3_minning_home_faq5_desc": "GT Staking is generally safe, but please be aware of the following: \n1. Node risk: Choosing a node with unstable block production may affect your actual earnings.\n2. Earnings fluctuation: Staking rewards may fluctuate based on node performance.\n3. Node scoring mechanism: A decrease in node score due to poor performance could impact your rewards ratio.\n4. Asset security: In extreme cases, technical vulnerabilities or attacks could affect asset security. The platform has introduced audits and risk controls to minimize such risks, but users are advised to assess and manage their investments prudently.",
