  "web3_minning_increase_earnings_q1_title": "What is node score?",
  "web3_minning_increase_earnings_q1_desc": "Node score (initially set at 1, with a maximum of 2) reflects the node's block production stability. The higher the score, the higher chances the node will be selected.\nEach time, three nodes are randomly selected for reward distribution. Nodes with higher scores are more likely to be selected, thus resulting in higher earning for users staking with them.",
  "web3_minning_increase_earnings_q2_title": "Does the total staked amount affect the return?",
  "web3_minning_increase_earnings_q2_desc": "The higher the total staked amount on a node, the greater its chance of producing blocks. However, your share of the rewards will be proportionally smaller.\nA node's block production probability is influenced by two key factors: total staked amount and node score. While nodes with higher total stakes have a better chance of receiving rewards, those rewards are distributed among more users—meaning your actual share of the reward may decrease.",
